                "description": "Prepare your rural property for technician arrival:\n\n**Pet & Livestock Considerations:**\n- Secure dogs (even friendly ones) that might be protective\n- Confine cats that might escape through open doors\n- Secure horses or livestock in paddocks away from work areas\n- Alert technician to any animals via special instructions\n- Consider pets' reaction to service vehicle and unfamiliar person\n\n**Family Notification:**\n- Let household members know technician will be working\n- Service may require multiple trips between indoor/outdoor equipment\n- May need to cycle heating on/off during diagnosis\n- Expect 45-120 minutes for diagnosis and repair\n\n**Why This Matters:** Secured animals prevent delays and ensure safety for technicians and pets. Rural properties often have more animals to consider than suburban homes.",
